# Path Aliases

This document outlines the path aliases used in the backend for easy module resolution.

## Configuration

Path aliases are defined in `packages/backend/tsconfig.json` under the `compilerOptions.paths` key.

## Available Aliases

-   `@routes/*`: `src/routes/*`
-   `@middlewares/*`: `src/middlewares/*`
-   `@common/*`: `src/common/*`
-   `@controllers/*`: `src/controllers/*`
-   `@models/*`: `src/models/*`
-   `@tests/*`: `src/tests/*`
-   `@js/*`: `src/js/*`
-   `@root/*`: `src/*`
-   `@bt/shared/*`: `../../shared/src/*`
-   `@services/*`: `src/services/*`

Always use these aliases when importing modules from these directories to maintain consistency and readability.
